<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in form • on form</xh5><p> <i>in form—</i>1. in structure: Cretan buildings are simple <u>in form</u>, conforming to architectural norms of Byzantine provenance. 2. in good physical or mental condition: Even if a horse is <u>in form</u> a bad trip almost surely will cancel its chances. 3. as a mere formality: The laws, which heretofore existed only <u>in form</u>, have been thoroughly enforced.</p><p><i>on form—</i>1. on the basis of previous results: <u>On form</u>, they have no chance of winning today. 2. <i>= in form 2: </i>We all knew that Michael was always <u>on form</u> when he played and he exceeded his own expectations today!</p> </entry>
